ing when set). Depending on the peer itself, the MultiplayerAPI will become a network server (check with ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/MultiplayerAPI\/isServer()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") and will set root node’s network mode to authority, or it will become a regular client peer. All child nodes are set to inherit the network mode by default. Handling of networking-related events (connection, disconnection, new clients) is done by connecting to MultiplayerAPI’s signals."}],"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"multiplayerPeer","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot15MultiplayerPeerC","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MultiplayerPeer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/multiplayerapi\/multiplayerpeer","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/MultiplayerAPI\/multiplayerPeer","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/VariantRepresentable":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"VariantRepresentable","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VariantRepresentable"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Types that conform to VariantRepresentable can be stored directly in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Variant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with no conversion.  These include all of the Variant types from Godot (for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example ","type":"text"},{"code":"GString","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Rect"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"Plane","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), Godot objects (those that subclass","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftGodot.Object) as well as the built-in Swift types UInt8, Int64 and Double."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","tex